                  <additions><!--THIS element in domlib CONTAINS ESCAPED HTML, thus it is not possible to reliably extract the information about pages. Please watch out.-->
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#35vb">Fols. 35vb-36</locus>rc: Tarik zä-täṣǝḥfä bä-mäwaʿǝlihomu lä-näguśä nägäśt Yoḥannǝs..., "History that was written in the time of the King of Kings Yoḥannǝs...", a short historiographic composition. <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note, in a mediocre hand, was written during the time of King Yoḥannǝs IV (r. 1872-89), nǝburä ʾǝd ʾIyasu and ʾabba Täklä Haymanot and ʾaläqa Täklä ʾƎsṭifanos from Gondär (the scribe?) "who was with them". The note is a list of metropolitans of the Ethiopian Orthodox Church from ʾabba Sälama to ʾabunä ʾAtnatewos (in tenure 1867-76), with description of some events. It contains 107 names. Besides, it mentions some rulers of Ethiopia and events that took place when they were in power, such as King Susǝnyos and the arrival of the Catholic priests, the restoration of the Orthodox faith, the rule of King ʾIyasu, the conflict between däğğazmač Wube and ras ʿAli, the death of ʾAtnatewos at ʿAdwa.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#181rb">Fol. 181rb</locus>-rc: Extensive donation note.<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note is written in the main hand. It states that the commissioner of the Ms. is ʾabba Gǝrma Ṣǝyon who donated it to the Däbrä Dammo monastery.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">-	The title ስንክሳር and the internal number of the monastic library (384) are written on fol. 1r. &#xD;
-	Four lines of the incipit of the Synaxarion are written four times on fol. 2r.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
